name: Ampharos
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, you may search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Lightning Pokemon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage. If tails, this attack does 40 damage and the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Blissey
AbilityText: When you play Blissey from your hand, you may flip a coin. If heads, remove 8 damage counters from Blissey. If tails, remove 4 damage counters from Blissey. Either way, if Blissey has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Celebi
AbilityText: If an opponent's attack would Knock Out Celebi, flip a coin. If heads, Celebi isn't Knocked Out and you shuffle it and all cards attached to it into your deck. This power doesn't work if Celebi is already Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, put 1 damage counter on the Defending Pokemon.

name: Crobat
Attack1Text: If your opponent attaches an Energy card to the Defending Pokemon during his or her next turn, that Pokemon becomes Poisoned.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads. If you get 2 or more heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Delibird
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. If exactly 1 is heads, this attack does 40 damage. If exactly 2 are heads, remove 3 damage counters from the Defending Pokemon. If the Defending Pokemon has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them. If all 3 are heads, this attack does 60 damage. If all 3 are tails, remove all damage counters from the Defending Pokemon.

name: Entei
AbilityText: When you play Entei from your hand, you may discard the top 5 cards of your deck. (If you have fewer cards in your deck than that, discard all of them.) If any of those are Fire Energy cards, attach them to any of your Fire Pokemon of your choice. Using this power ends your turn.
Attack1Text: Discard 2 Fire Energy cards attached to Entei or this attack does nothing.

name: Ho-oh
Attack1Text: You may search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to Ho-Oh. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

name: Houndoom
Attack1Text: Discard 1 Fire Energy card attached to Houndoom or this attack does nothing. If there are any Darkness Energy cards in your discard pile, attach 1 of them to Houndoom.
Attack2Text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Darkness Energy attached to Houndoom. This attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads.

name: Jumpluff
Attack1Text: Choose any number of your Hoppips and Skiplooms. Then, for each Pokemon you chose in this way, you may search your deck for a card that evolves from that Pokemon and attach it to that Pokemon. (This counts as evolving those Pokemon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Magneton
AbilityText: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may take 1 Energy card attached to 1 of your Magnemites, Magnetons, or Dark Magnetons and attach it to a different 1 of your Magnemites, Magnetons, and Dark Magnetons. This power can't be used if Magneton is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: If there are any Lightning Energy cards in your discard pile, attach 1 of them to Magneton.

name: Misdreavus
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon is Asleep and was attacked with Night Eyes during your last turn, it is Knocked Out.

name: Porygon2
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may choose 1 basic Energy card attached to 1 of your Pokemon and choose an Energy type. Treat that Energy card as that type until the end of your turn. This power can't be used if Porygon2 is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed. If Porygon2 becomes Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed, the Energy card goes back to its original type.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose whether the Defending Pokemon becomes Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Raikou
AbilityText: Whenever you attach a Lightning Energy card from your hand to Raikou, if your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with the Defending Pokemon. This power stops working while Raikou is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, Raikou does 20 damage to itself.

name: Suicune
AbilityText: Prevent all effects of your opponent's attacks, other than damage, done to Suicune. This power stops working while Suicune is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. If both are heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed. If only 1 is heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Aerodactyl
AbilityText: Whenever an Evolved Pokemon attacks (even if it's your opponent's), it can use any attack from its Basic Pokemon card or any Evolution card attached to it. It still has to pay for that attack's Energy cost. This power stops working while Aerodactyl is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Aerodactyl. If tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).

name: Celebi
Attack1Text: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon. This attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads. Remove a number of damage counters from Celebi equal to the damage done to the Defending Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance). If Celebi has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

name: Entei
AbilityText: As long as Entei is your Active Pokemon, Entei and Energy cards attached to it aren't affected by effects from Trainer cards other than Stadium cards. As long as this Power is active, discard any Trainer cards attached to Entei. (This power works even if Entei is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.)
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. For each tails, discard 1 Fire Energy card from Entei, if it has any.

name: Ho-oh
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each type of Basic Energy card, if any, attached to Ho-Oh.

name: Kingdra
Attack1Text: Use any attack from Kingdra's Basic Pokemon card or Evolution card. (Kingdra doesn't have to pay for that attack's Energy cost.)
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, choose 1 Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon, if any, and discard it. If both are tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).

name: Lugia
Attack1Text: You may flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 80 damage. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Raichu
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: You may discard all Lightning Energy cards attached to Raichu. If you do, this attack does 80 damage.

name: Raikou
AbilityText: As long as Raikou is your Active Pokemon, Raikou and Energy cards attached to it aren't affected by effects from Trainer cards other than Stadium cards. As long as this Power is active, discard any Trainer cards attached to Raikou. (This power works even if Raikou is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.)
Attack1Text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of them and this attack does 20 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Skarmory
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Skarmory.

name: Sneasel
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard all Trainer cards attached to your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Starmie
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Choose an Energy type other than Colorless. This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon with any Energy cards of that type attached to it. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

name: Sudowoodo
AbilityText: As long as Sudowoodo is your Active Pokemon, it copies all of the Defending Pokemon's attacks, including their costs. This power can't be used if Sudowoodo is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Suicune
AbilityText: As long as Suicune is your Active Pokemon, Suicune and Energy cards attached to it aren't affected by effects from Trainer cards other than Stadium cards. As long as this Power is active, discard any Trainer cards attached to Suicune. (This power works even if Suicune is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.)
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage. If tails, this attack does 30 damage and, if your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with the Defending Pokemon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokemon.)

name: Flaaffy
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Golbat
Attack1Text: Until the end of your next turn, if an attack damages the Defending Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), that attack does 20 more damage to the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If this attack damages the Defending Pokemon, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned and you remove a number of damage counters from Golbat equal to half that damage (rounded up to the nearest 10). If Golbat has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them. Either way, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Graveler
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage to each of your own Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Don't apply Resistance.

name: Jynx
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage and the Defending Pokemon is now Confused. If tails, this attack does 20 damage.

name: Lanturn
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may change Lanturn's type to Water until the end of your turn. This power can't be used if Lanturn is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed. If Lanturn becomes Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed after you have used this power, its type changes back to Lightning.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Magcargo
AbilityText: If Magcargo is your Active Pokemon and moves to the Bench, remove 1 Fire Energy card attached to Magcargo, if any, and attach it to the new Active Pokemon. (You can't choose an Energy card that you used to pay the Retreat Cost.)
Attack1Text: You may discard any number of Fire Energy cards attached to Magcargo when you use this attack. If you do, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage for each Fire Energy card you discarded in this way.

name: Octillery
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, whenever the Defending Pokemon attacks, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing. (Benching or evolving that Pokemon ends this effect.)

name: Parasect
AbilityText: As long as Parasect is in play, cards in any player's discard piles are not affected by attacks or Pokemon Powers. This power stops working if Parasect becomes Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Piloswine
Attack1Text: Remove 3 damage counters from Piloswine. If it has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.
Attack2Text: Piloswine does 30 damage to itself. Piloswine can't use this attack during your next turn.

name: Seaking
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage. If tails, this attack does 10 damage.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. If both are heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 40 more damage. If 1 or both of them are tails, this attack does 20 damage.

name: Stantler
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Basic Pokemon, choose 1 of its attacks. That Pokemon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: If you have any Benched Pokemon, flip a coin. If tails, this attack does 10 damage to 1 of them. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Unown [B]
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Pokemon with Unown in its name to Unown [B]. This power can't be used if Unown [B] has 10 HP left. This power can be used even if Unown [B] is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Unown [Y]
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Psychic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokemon with Unown in its name. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can be used even if Unown [Y] is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Aipom
Attack1Text: Choose a Trainer card attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. Your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck.

name: Chinchou
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage. If tails, this attack does 10 damage.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon attacks Chinchou during your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Chinchou is reduced by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance). (Benching or evolving either Pokemon ends this effect.)

name: Farfetch'd
Attack2Text: This attack can't be used during your next turn. (Benching Farfetch'd ends this effect.)

name: Goldeen
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Murkrow
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon card named Murkrow and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward. (You can't use this attack if your Bench is full.)
Attack2Text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Murkrows on your Bench. This attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads.

name: Paras
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Quagsire
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon has any Energy cards attached to it, choose 1 of them and discard it.

name: Qwilfish
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads you get.

name: Remoraid
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

name: Shuckle
AbilityText: Whenever an attack (including your own) does 40 or less damage to Shuckle (after applying Weakness and Resistance), reduce that damage to 10. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.) This power stops working while Shuckle is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned. It now takes 20 Poison damage instead of 10 after each player's turn (even if it was already Poisoned).

name: Skiploom
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Slugma
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Smoochum
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a Special Energy card attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. Your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck.

name: Snubbull
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 damage times the number of damage counters on Snubbull. If tails, this attack does 10 damage.

name: Staryu
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Swinub
Attack2Text: Swinub does 10 damage to itself.

name: Unown [K]
AbilityText: Your opponent's attacks, Pokemon Powers, and Trainer cards can't discard Energy cards from your Pokemon with Unown in their names. (Any other effects still happen.)

name: Zubat
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.
